{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, meta prompting [55] uses a language model as an orchestrator, dividing complex tasks and invoking experts, i.e., language models that are either fine-tuned or have received specific instructions to solve a specific type of problems.The scope of such systems goes beyond prompt engineering and, thus, beyond the goals of Impromptu.",
    "Instead, Impromptu aims to support multimodal applications and emphasizes simplicity in creating, managing and reusing prompts.Other tools and services aim to improve the quality and security of the response generation process.",
    "On one hand, they validate the input prompt, detecting potential lowquality or malicious user prompts.",
    "On the other hand, they aim to validate generative AI responses, that is, doublechecking that the response fulfills the requirements of the prompt's writer, either if they are implicit (clarity, lack of toxicity, …) or explicit (described in the prompt).",
    "Some examples of such systems are Guardrails AI [56] or NeMo Guardrails [57], and they define both quality criteria and corrective actions, e.g., regenerating the same prompt or patching the prompt with new instructions to avoid the detected defect."
  ]
}